Project Structure and Organization

my-app/
├── public/
│   ├── index.html
│   └── assets/
├── src/
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── common/
│   │   └── specific/
│   ├── hooks/
│   ├── pages/
│   ├── services/
│   ├── store/
│   ├── styles/
│   ├── utils/
│   ├── App.tsx
│   ├── index.tsx
│   └── routes.tsx
├── tests/
├── .gitignore
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
└── README.md


Explanation
- public: Contains static assets like - index.html, images, and other public resources.
- src/: Main source code direcotry
  - components/: Reusable UI components, further divided into common/ (shared across multiple parts) and specific/ (specific to certain features).
  - hooks/: Custom React hooks.
  - pages/: Page components corresponding to routes.
  - services/: API calls and business logic.
  - store/: State management setup (e.g., Redux).
  - styles/: Global styles, theming, and CSS/SASS files.
  - utils/: Utility functions and helpers.
  - App.tsx: Root component.
  - index.tsx: Entry point.
  - routes.tsx: Route definitions.
